The Minister of Basic Education, Angie Motshekga, to brief on the state of readiness for schools in the context of COVID-19. The Minister will also provide details and answer questions on all matters affecting the basic education sector.  JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga will outline her department’s plans for 2021. The minister is expected to give an update of the state of readiness of schools in the context of COVID-19. READ: Motshekga: We hope learners got all the support needed for final exams Schools are expected to open later than normal next year. According to the school calendar sent out in October, pupils are set to return on 27 January.